title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 3.76 - Executive Order No. 76: Designating the Empire State Plaza in Albany to be The Governor Nelson A. Rockefeller Empire State Plaza
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 3.76 - Executive Order No. 76: Designating the Empire State Plaza in Albany to be The Governor Nelson A. Rockefeller Empire State Plaza

State Regulations
I, Hugh L. Carey, Governor of the State of New York, by
virtue of the authority vested in me by the Constitution and laws of the State
of New York, and in order to memorialize by fitting tribute the role of former

Governor Nelson A. Rockefeller in the conception and construction of the
spectacular complex of buildings forming the seat of State government in

Albany, do hereby order and declare that the plaza known since its dedication
on November 21, 1973 as the Empire State Plaza, shall henceforth be known as

The Governor Nelson A. Rockefeller Empire State Plaza. Signed: Hugh L. Carey

Dated: October 6, 1978
